Package: collatR
Title: Collate Source Code for LLM Analysis
Version: 0.1.0
Author: Emily O'Grady
Maintainer: Emily O'Grady <emilyogrady21@gmail.com>
Description: A tool to scan a local or remote code repository (especially R packages), 
    find all relevant source files, and combine them into a single, well-structured 
    text file. This is ideal for pasting the entire context of a project into a Large 
    Language Model (LLM) for debugging, analysis, or refactoring.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Encoding: UTF-8
RoxygenNote: 7.3.2
Imports: 
    cli,
    clipr,
    gert,
    rappdirs,
    withr
Suggests:
    mockery,
    testthat (>= 3.0.0)
Config/testthat/edition: 3
